original: Lindberg, Karl Georg, advokat, Göteborg, f. 23/4/97 i Eksjö av und:löjtn. Carl L. o. Anna Hultquist. G. 36 m. Mary Lindeberg. Barn: Birgitta f. 36, Ingemar 44. — Stud:ex. i Växjö 17, jur. kand. i Sthlm 23. E. o. not. i Göta hovr. 23, tingstjg. i Norra o. Södra Vedbo hds doms. 24-25, adv. i Gbg sed. 25. Led. av Sv:es adv:samf. sed. 28.
translated: Lindberg, Karl Georg, lawyer, Gothenburg, born April 23, 1897 in Eksjö, to the late lieutenant Carl L. and Anna Hultquist. Married in 1936 to Mary Lindeberg. Children: Birgitta, born in 1936, Ingemar, born in 1944. Completed secondary school in Växjö in 1917, obtained a law degree in Stockholm in 1923. Became a junior clerk and notary at the Gothenburg Court of Appeal in 1923, served as a district court clerk in the North and South Vedbo judicial district from 1924-1925, and has been practicing as a lawyer in Gothenburg since 1925. Became a member of the Swedish Lawyers Association in 1928.
